optional.

boundaries, which can be used to define special price types and subsidies.

supervising the overall usage of iLab.

Institutional Administrators have certain rights within iLab

that allow them to report at the institutional level and allows them to manage users and groups

within their organization.

Principal Investigator (PI): Primary leader of a lab or group within iLab.</source>

250. This means that any internal

1. Observe the symptom  
   – Note exactly what’s happening (for example, “GC Not Ready” messages or abnormal output signals).

   – Diagnostics tab displays detected issues and offers automated troubleshooting.  
   – Run Diagnostic Tests (Diagnostics > Diagnostic Tests) for more information.  
4. Generate and review the System Health Report  
   – Lists current status of all GC components, firmware version, serial number, and recent self-diagnostic results.  
5. Check logs  
   – View the Run Log and System Log for error messages and events.  
6. Narrow down causes  
   – Check each possible cause or perform tests until the symptom is resolved.  
7. Contact Agilent if needed  
   – Have your System Health Report and logs ready when you call for service.
